President Obama announced the charitable organizations that will receive a portion of the $1.4 million awarded by the Nobel Peace Prize. The organizations include the Hispanic Scholarship Fund, Fisher House, the Clinton-Bush Fund for Haiti, College Summit, the Posse Foundation, the United Negro College Fund, the Appalachian Leadership and Education Foundation (ALEF), the American Indian College Fund, AfriCare, and the Central Asia Institute. These organizations provide support in various areas such as education, healthcare, and community development.